By Emmanuel Mogbede The All Progressives Congress (APC) has commenced the screening of its aspirants for 2023 presidential election. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the screening which is presently taking place at the Transcop Hilton Hotel, Abuja would last for two days. A source in the party said its former National Chairman,Â  Chief John Odigie Oyegun, woud lead the seven-man Presidential Screening Committee (PSC).